metric_description: Total number of the unacknowledged messages (a.k.a. backlog messages) for a subscription in a given topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.

Total quota byte size of the unacknowledged messages (a.k.a. backlog messages) for a subscription in a given topic partition.. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.
Age (in seconds) of the oldest unacknowledged message retained for a subscription in a given topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.
Cumulative count of messages sent to subscribers for a subscription in a given topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.

Cumulative quota byte size of messages sent to subscribers for a subscription in a given topic partition. See https://cloud.google.com/pubsub/lite/quotas#resource_quotas for quota byte calculation. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
Cumulative byte size of messages sent to subscribers for a subscription in a given topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
Age (in seconds) of the oldest message retained in a topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.
Cumulative count of published messages in a topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
The maximum number of message bytes that can be published per second per topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.

Cumulative quota byte size of published messages in a topic partition. See https://cloud.google.com/pubsub/lite/quotas#resource_quotas for quota byte calculation. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.

The ratio of the rate of message quota bytes that are being published to a partition to the rate that can be published per topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
Cumulative byte size of published messages in a topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
Cumulative count of publish requests in a topic partition, broken down by response code. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.

Cumulative quota byte size of messages sent to subscribers for a topic partition. See https://cloud.google.com/pubsub/lite/quotas#resource_quotas for quota byte calculation. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
The quota byte limit for message storage in a topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.
The maximum number of message bytes that can be received by subscribers per second per topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 120 seconds.

The ratio of the rate of message quota bytes that are sent to subscribers for a partition to the rate that can be received per topic partition. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling, data is not visible for up to 210 seconds.
